Tenerife's midfield powerhouse Fernando Redondo has  been offrered a four-year contract by Spanish giants Real Madrid.
The transfer of the Argentinian player was announced jointly by the Club  chairmen Ramon Mendoza and Javier Perez in the Spanish capital on Tuesday.
Real Madrid are reported to have offered 3.8 million dollars and two  players in exchange for Redondo. One of the players involved in the exchange  is reserve team player Victor Manuel Fernandez. The other will be named  shortly.
Real also agreed to play a friendly with Tenerife at Santa Cruz.
